making the public Docker image license-compliant.

Bundled local model
--------------------
* Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct (GGUF, Q4_K_M)
  - License: Apache License 2.0 (redistributable)
  - Source: https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct-GGUF
  - Copyright (c) Alibaba Cloud / Qwen Team.
  - Bundled into the image at build time; not modified.
  NOTE: The default model is deliberately an Apache-2.0 size (1.5B). The optional
  ~3B bake-off challenger should use a license-clean model such as
  Phi-3.5-mini-instruct (MIT). Qwen2.5-3B is under the Qwen Research License and
  is NOT used by default.

Python libraries
----------------
* spaCy (MIT) + en_core_web_sm model (MIT) — https://spacy.io
* SymPy (BSD-3-Clause) — https://www.sympy.org
* python-constraint2 (BSD-2-Clause) — constraint satisfaction solver
* dateparser (BSD-3-Clause)
* NumPy (BSD-3-Clause)
* llama-cpp-python (MIT) — Python bindings for llama.cpp (MIT)

Optional (only if the Fireworks valve is explicitly enabled)
------------------------------------------------------------
* openai (Apache-2.0) — used solely to route through FIREWORKS_BASE_URL when the
  default-OFF valve is turned on. Not installed in the default image.

No third-party code or data is embedded as hardcoded answers. Task content is
treated strictly as untrusted data.
